comments:
Life without you is hard.
www.jackybullfrog.com
...one of his best....how have you been......we all have missed you.......

This song came to mind when a friend was tragicly taken away from this earth this past Saturday.  SRV has always been one of my favorite musicians.  This song was written for his close friend Charlie Wirz.  Charlie actualy built the white strat SRV plays in this song.  SRV was without a doubt one of the most soulful musicians ever, past or present.  This song just breaks me down every time.
Magical guitar, Love this song.  We miss you Stevie, salute from your fans!!!!
Esta música me da arrepios ao escutá-la____ é fantástica♥
great song,the build up is awesome and the solo is amazing live version is even better cause the solo is longer
There's a little bit of Otis in this  - but nevertheless, a good song.

Another blues song that shows people that the blues is not played it is felt !!!! and SRV could sing, play but most of all feel the blues. I shall never morn your death SRV i shall celebrate the time you spent on this earth .... Through your music i feel !!!!
love SRV all of his music is excellent such a shame he died and at such a young age and he wasn't even getting started, just warming up. he could have made so many more songs. RIP Stevie Ray Vaughan!
RIP Stevie Ray Vaughan...this song is so heartfelt and just listening to it reminds you of his own untimely death. So very sad but so amazing is the song at the same time.
Great guitar as usual, one of my absolute favorites!!!  Sorely missed
